article.title: Algebras of bounded noncommutative analytic functions on subvarieties of the noncommutative unit ball

multiple_choice_question.text: What does the formula  K(Z, W)(T) =  ∑_(k∈Wd)  Z^(k)TW^(∗k) represent?
choices: The definition of a noncommutative algebraic variety.
The distance formula for noncommutative functions.
The reproducing property of kernel functions.

multiple_choice_question.text: What is Wd in the formula K(Z, W)(T) =  ∑_(k∈Wd)  Z^(k)TW^(∗k)?
choices: The set of all n x n matrices.
The free monoid on d generators.
The d-dimensional open matrix unit ball.
The set of all d-tuples of n x n matrices.

multiple_choice_question.text: What types of matrices are Z and W in the formula K(Z, W)(T) =  ∑_(k∈Wd)  Z^(k)TW^(∗k)?
choices: Matrices belonging to the noncommutative unit ball.
Matrices with entries from a C*-algebra.

multiple_choice_question.text: What does the kernel K(Z, W)(T) define?
choices: A noncommutative reproducing kernel Hilbert space.
